did.unittitle: Indiana University News-Letter
did.abstract: This collection consists of a mostly-complete run of the Indiana University News-Letter from 1913 to 1945. The newsletter, originally titled Alumni News-Letter of Indiana University, was a monthly publication primarily used to communicate Indiana University news with alumni.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for research. Advance notice required.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: The Indiana University News-letter was a monthly publication that was used primarily to communicate with Indiana University alumni. It began as the Alumni News-letter of Indiana University in 1913. The university began using the title "Indiana University News-letter" with either the second or third issue of 1914. Issues were usually thematic, focusing on current events at the university and in the world.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: The collection consists of newsletters published from 1913 to 1945. Topics include current world events, such as World War I, and Indiana University happenings, such as athletic events and homecoming festivities. In addition, the newsletters often contain appeals to alumni for participation in alumni affairs as well as financial support for projects such as the Memorial Fund campaign.

The run of newsletters is mostly complete, lacking only the following issues: vol. II, no. 2 (1914), vol. III, no. 9 (1915), vol. IV, no. 1 (1916), vol. VI, no. 3 (1918), vol. VII, no. 8 (1919), vol. VIII, no. 6 (1920), vol. XVIII, no. 1 (1930), vol. XXV, no. 12 (1937), and vol. XXVI, no. 12 (1938).

relatedmaterial.head: Related Material
relatedmaterial.p: Some issues of the News-letter are available digitally through Hathi-Trust.

userestrict.head: Usage Restrictions
userestrict.p: Copyrights for records originating with Indiana University administrative units, departments, and other offices are held by the Trustees of Indiana University. For more information, please contact the Indiana University Archives staff.

The Indiana University Archives respects the intellectual property rights of others and does not claim any copyrights for non-university records, materials in the public domain, or materials for which we do not hold a Deed of Gift. Responsibility for the determination of the copyright status of these materials rests with those persons wishing to reuse the materials. Researchers are responsible for securing permission from copyright owners and any other rights holders for any reuse of these materials that extends beyond fair use or other statutory limitations.

Digital reproductions of archival materials from the Indiana University Archives are made available for noncommercial educational and research purposes only. If you are the copyright holder for any of the digitized materials and have questions about its inclusion on our site, please contact the Indiana University Archivist.
